cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the problem of association and relaying in millimeter wave networks, which is a topic related to network communication and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a stochastic optimization problem and distributed auction algorithms, which are related to control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper focuses on the specific characteristics of millimeter wave networks, such as blockage and deafness, which are related to the physical layer of the network, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for load balancing at access points, which is related to distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category as well.
